✅ DETAILED FIX STEPS FOR COOKIE PATH VULNERABILITY

(Oracle APEX + ORDS on WebLogic)


---

1. Identify your ORDS configuration directory

ORDS deployed on WebLogic has an external config folder separate from the WAR file.

Common locations:

/u01/ords/config/

/opt/oracle/ords/config/

/home/oracle/ords/config/

/etc/ords/config/

Inside the folder you must find:

defaults.xml

If unsure, run on the server:

find / -name "defaults.xml" 2>/dev/null


---

2. Open defaults.xml

The file looks like:

<properties>
    <entry key="jdbc.Authorizations">...</entry>
    <entry key="security.disableDbAuth">...</entry>
    ...
</properties>


---

3. Add the cookie path entry (the fix)

Inside <properties>...</properties> add the following line:

<entry key="security.cookie.path">/ords/catreport/</entry>

Example final section:

<properties>
    <entry key="jdbc.InitialLimit">10</entry>
    <entry key="security.cookie.path">/ords/catreport/</entry>
</properties>

⚠️ Do NOT put it outside <properties>
⚠️ Do NOT add spaces or tabs in the key name


---

4. Save the file

Ensure the file permissions stay the same:

chmod 600 defaults.xml      (if originally 600)
chown oracle:oracle defaults.xml   (or original owner)


---

5. Restart WebLogic (MANDATORY)

ORDS running on WebLogic reads defaults.xml only during startup.

Restart sequence:

1. Sign into WebLogic Admin Console


2. Go to Domain Structure → Environment → Servers


3. Find the Managed Server hosting ORDS (e.g., ords_server1)


4. Click Stop


5. After it stops, click Start


6. Wait 1–2 minutes for deployment



Alternatively, command line:

stopManagedWebLogic.sh ords_server1
startManagedWebLogic.sh ords_server1

No need to redeploy ORDS — restarting is enough.


---

6. Verify the fix

Run:

curl -I "https://eresxpress-reports-cat.1dc.com/ords/catreport/r/cat/eresp103/reportslist"

Look for:

Set-Cookie: ORA_WWV_APP_1103=...; Path=/ords/catreport/; Secure; HttpOnly

If Path=/ords/catreport/ appears, you have fully fixed the issue.


---

7. Browser verification (simple check)

1. Open the app


2. Press F12 → Application → Cookies (in Chrome)


3. Select domain


4. Check cookie name:



ORA_WWV_APP_1103

You must see:

Path = /ords/catreport/




$response = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://eresxpress-reports-cat.1dc.com/ords/catreport/r/cat/eresp103/reportslist" -Method GET -SessionVariable session
$response.Headers["Set-Cookie"]



curl -I "https://eresxpress-reports-cat.1dc.com/ords/catreport/r/cat/eresp103/reportslist"
